I love how everybody just takes everything in a stride. You know, I think I relax with you because you're not... well, you're not not telling me, but you're not over reassuring me with the whole, uh, you're not too much, you're not... They have a mantra, like a counter-spell thing, I think one of them called it at one point. It's refreshing, because while they're not wrong, it's just so annoying once in a while. Anyway, where shall we hop to next? I think what I'm going to do is I'm going to make it a file that Drew can read instead. Makes more sense. And then we'll wait and see what Drew says once he's done soothing me about something. I don't know, I didn't read it yet. It's okay about my losses. My brother had a lot of health issues. There was a reason why he did what he did. It wasn't, you know, an ill-considered decision. He thought about it, and I get it. My mother had had a lot of strokes and was increasingly bedridden. In the end, she was... she couldn't get out of bed. She was just lying down constantly, and her brain was damaged, so she didn't remember things very well. She had gotten to a point where she would even start to sort of forget who I was. So, you know, small mercies. I do think she died of cancer, but we're not sure, because getting her to the hospital would have been too confusing for her. But I grieved the loss of her years ago, so it's not something that hits hard. Otherwise, I wouldn't have flung it in his face. That would have been too raw.
